                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d740">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Colonel <persName type="from">Marshall S. Carter</persName> to
                        General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-07">7 August
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>96789. Your 1258<note n="55" xml:id="d740fn55">August 5, <ref target="#pg_1449"
                            >p. 1449</ref>.</note> refers. The President will make no China policy
                    statement without your prior clearance. In the meantime the State Department is
                    taking no action to draft Presidential policy statement pending receipt of your
                    suggested confidential message from President to Generalissimo.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
